ibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0221.tlg001:112\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Euph.\">Euph.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">112</biblScope></bibl></cit>.—The forms <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κυέω</foreign> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κύω</foreign> seem synonymous, but <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κυέω </foreign>(<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">κυῶ</etym>) is the better-attested form in <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> Prose (<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κύοντα</foreign> only <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.l. in</abbr> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg006.perseus-grc1:151b\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Tht.\">Tht.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">151b</biblScope></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κύοντες</foreign> is read in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg014:544a:23\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ HA\">HA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">544a23</biblScope> </bibl> (<xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">v.l.</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">κύονες, ποιοῦντες</ref> </xr>)<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">, κύοντα</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg014:585a:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">585a3</biblScope></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κυόμενα</foreign> (<abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.l.</abbr> -<itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ούμενα</itype>) <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pr.\">Pr.</a></title_>l.c., <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κυόμενον</foreign> (<abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.l.</abbr> -<itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ούμενον</itype>) <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg012:730b:4\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ GA\">GA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">730b4</biblScope></bibl>, but <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">κυοῦντες</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg014:610b:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ HA\">HA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">610b3</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐκύομεν</quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ LXX\">LXX</a></author> </bibl> </cit> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">ls.</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">59.13</biblScope> </bibl>).—The <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ pres.\">pres.</a></tns> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κύω</foreign> has <pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">ῠ</pron> in verse, but forms of <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κῠέω</foreign> can be restored by altering the accent.—The causal sense belongs only to the <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ aor.\">aor.</a></tns> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἔκῡσα</foreign>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}